The paper deals with decoding of LDPC codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of the low-complexity majority algorithm suggests a focus on networking and communication (cs.NI). The modification of the algorithm and the derivation of a lower estimate on the decoding radius suggest a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The analysis of the complexity of the algorithm suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the use of LDPC codes in communication systems suggests a focus on computer communications (cs.CC).
